Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defendant Bambi Lee Tucker in court with attorney Dawn Marie Rablin.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

**COURT VACATED THE STAYED BENCH WARRANT FROM THE PREVIOUS DATE**

Statements made as to sentencing by State, Defense and Defendant.

Defendant sentenced to serve THIRTY (30) DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for TWO (2) DAYS time served.  Huber privileges for work and treatment.  Court approved Electronic Monitoring subject to HoC screening.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of ONE (1) YEAR.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:

* Mental Health Evaluation and take all prescribed medications.
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol.
* Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs, surcharges and supervision fees or CIVIL JUDGMENT will be entered WITH tax intercept.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
